715100f-b.text:
(1) East on 115th Street, west from the Harlem Rover and showing clearance of the former plant of the Standard G&S Light Co. Notice Gas tanks at the S.E. corner of Pleasant Ave. The row of buildings on the right are on the east side of Pleasant Ave., between 115th and 116th Streets.

September 12, 1934

P.L. Sperr

(2) The same, from a different angle. Building shown on the extreme right is a plant of the N.Y. Ice Co., and fronts onto East 116th Street.

September 12, 1934

P.L. Sperr

(3) The same as No. 2, at a later date.

November 9, 1934

P.L. Sperr
